description:
**File**: src/tui/handlers/action_handlers/selection.rs (around line 48, function handle_swap_keys)

**Discovered**: reviewer-minimax during LazyQMK-aopx.2 review.

The TUI Shift+W key handler has the IDENTICAL bug pattern that was just fixed in web/mod.rs::swap_keys:

```rust
// Current (buggy - loses 3 fields):
layer.keys[idx1].keycode = layer.keys[idx2].keycode;
layer.keys[idx1].color_override = layer.keys[idx2].color_override;
layer.keys[idx1].category_id = layer.keys[idx2].category_id;
// label, combo_participant, description NOT swapped
```

Same fix as LazyQMK-aopx.2: replace field copy with `layer.keys.swap(idx1, idx2)`.

**Risk**: Same as web fix - silent data loss. Users swapping keys in the TUI lose label/description/combo_participant.

Add as follow-up to keep LazyQMK-aopx.2 focused, then close this independently.

**File**: src/web/mod.rs:1755-1769

```rust
layer.keys[idx1].keycode         = second_key.keycode;
layer.keys[idx1].color_override  = second_key.color_override;
layer.keys[idx1].category_id     = second_key.category_id;
// label, description, combo_participant NOT swapped
```

`KeyDefinition` (src/models/layer.rs:96-115) has 7 fields. Swap silently drops 3 — most importantly `description`, which users actually fill in to document thumb keys etc.

**Fix**: Swap whole structs (`layer.keys.swap(idx1, idx2)` if positions are equal, which they must be for key keys within same layer), OR copy all 7 fields.

Also: 8 `eprintln!` debug calls at src/web/mod.rs:1722-1742 need to be removed.

**File**: src/tui/mod.rs:935-942 (`run_tui`)

```rust
if event::poll(Duration::from_millis(100))? {
    if let Event::Key(key) = event::read()? {        // consumes event
        ...
    } else if let Event::Resize(_, _) = event::read()? {  // blocks for NEXT event!
        // Terminal resized
    }
}
```

When the queue holds a non-Key event (Resize, Mouse, Focus), the first `event::read()` consumes it, the `if let` fails, and the `else if` calls `event::read()` again — which blocks indefinitely until the next event arrives (no timeout). Subsequent events get consumed by the wrong branch.

**Reproduce**: Run TUI, focus window changes mid-input, observe input lag.

**Fix**: Read once into a local, then match.
```rust
if event::poll(Duration::from_millis(100))? {
    match event::read()? {
        Event::Key(key) => { ... }
        Event::Resize(_, _) => { ... }
        _ => {}
    }
}
```

**Files**: src/tui/handlers/popups.rs (1801 lines, 19 popup variants), src/tui/handlers/{category,layer,settings,tap_dance,main}.rs

Pattern observed in current dispatch:
```rust
if let Some(ActiveComponent::KeycodePicker(ref mut picker)) = state.active_component {
    if let Some(event) = picker.handle_input(key, &state.keycode_db) {
        return handle_keycode_picker_event(state, event);
    }
}
```

This pattern (extract picker from ActiveComponent enum, call handle_input, dispatch event handler) is repeated for every popup. Extract a helper trait/function:

```rust
fn dispatch<T, F>(component: &mut Option<ActiveComponent>, state: &mut AppState,
                   key: KeyEvent, f: F) -> Result<bool>
where F: FnOnce(&mut T, ...) -> Result<()>;
```

Or define a common interface that all components implement so dispatch is uniform.

This is the meta-refactor for LazyQMK-aopx.4.7 once individual popups are clarified.

**File**: src/firmware/generator.rs:2523

A TODO comment with ~20 lines of commented-out test code:

```rust
// TODO: Re-enable these tests once encoder_count field is added to KeyboardGeometry
// #[test]
// fn test_generate_encoder_map_with_zero_encoders() { ... }
// #[test]
// fn test_generate_encoder_map_with_one_encoder() { ... }
// (+ more commented tests)
```

Searches elsewhere in the codebase would confirm:
1. Whether `encoder_count` is on `KeyboardGeometry` yet (probably not, hence the TODO)
2. Whether `generate_conditional_encoder_map` is being tested now via the inline test_setup or other tests

**Fix**: Either implement `encoder_count` on `KeyboardGeometry` + uncomment + add the tests, OR delete the block. If kept as future work, file a tracking issue (which is what this is) and just delete the commented code.

**Files**:
- src/parser/layout.rs — 3 `Regex::new(...).unwrap()` per call
- src/parser/template_gen.rs — `Regex::new(r'...').unwrap()` inside helpers (line 2163, 2199, 2232)
- src/parser/keyboard_json.rs — multiple

Compilation runs on every invocation of these functions. For a hot path called repeatedly during layout parse, this is wasteful.

**Fix**:
```rust
use std::sync::OnceLock;

fn tag_regex() -> &'static Regex {
    static RE: OnceLock<Regex> = OnceLock::new();
    RE.get_or_init(|| Regex::new(r"^[a-z0-9-]+$").unwrap())
}

// Call site
let re = tag_regex();
re.is_match(tag)
```

Or with `once_cell::sync::Lazy` if preferred.
